02/06/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- SFOR reported Friday (30 May) that it has launched a lottery for those in BiH who turn in weapons voluntarily. 
Anyone who surrenders a rifle will get five tickets for the raffle. 
A grenade or a grenade launcher gets its owner three tickets and 20 rounds of ammunition get one ticket. 
The lottery will run until 22 June, with the top prize being a car. 
About 8,500 lottery tickets have been given out. 
(Reuters - 30/05/03)
